    <div class="body">
        <p>Initially I should note, that in case this is caused because I am doing something wrong, I am sorry in advance.</p>

<p>I've created a custom controller Plugin which in the preDispatch() under some circumstances, changes the $request object parameters to redirect the request to a different module/controller/action as such:</p>

<p>$request-&gt;setModuleName('module')
    -&gt;setControllerName('controller')
    -&gt;setActionName('action')
    -&gt;setParam('param', 'value')
    -&gt;setDispatched(false);</p>

<p>If the module/controller/action throws an Exception I log it via the ErrorController. However while trying to log via the FirePHP Writer, the writer goes into an endless loop in the encodeObject() function.</p>

